SIMPLE: yerk
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yerk
<hw>Yerk</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Yerked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Yerking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See <er>Yerk</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To throw or thrust with a sudden, smart movement; to
kick or strike suddenly; to jerk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their wounded steeds . . . ⟦br⟧
<qex>Yerk</qex> out their armed heels at their dead masters.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To strike or lash with a whip.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yerk</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Yerk
<hw>Yerk</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To throw out the heels;
to kick; to jerk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They flirt, they <qex>yerk</qex>, they backward . . . fling.</q>
<rj><qau>Drayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To move a quick, jerking motion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yerk</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Yerk
<hw>Yerk</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A sudden or quick thrust or motion; a
jerk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yern</ent>⟦br⟧
